  "body": "It would be nice to separate execution payloads in DB to reduce post-merge disk usage and not store finalized execution payloads in prysm DB.\r\n\r\nSome food for thoughts...\r\n\r\n- Should we support backs compatible with networks that have already merged?\r\n- Address the many places that previously use full blocks and now are switching to blind blocks (API, block replay, p2p)\r\n- Do we migrate on per block level, per epoch level, or per finalization level?\r\n- How do we utilize new `get_payload_by_block_hash` method that reconstructs a payload using the EE's `eth_getBlockByHash call`\r\n- Performance test, we should measure the latency of blocks-by-root and blocks-by-range responses\r\n- E2e test, we should test payload <-> header reconstructions",
